  "prompt": "He keeps turning to look at me. If a guy does this, does that mean he's interested in you?",
  "response": "When a guy keeps turning to look at you, it *could* be a sign of interest, but it doesn\u2019t always mean that definitively. Here are some possibilities to consider:\n\n1. **He\u2019s Interested**: If he\u2019s repeatedly looking at you, especially with lingering glances or smiles, it might mean he\u2019s attracted to you or curious about you.  \n   \n2. **He\u2019s Curious**: He might be wondering why you\u2019re looking at *him* (if you\u2019ve also been glancing his way) or he could simply be intrigued by something about you.\n\n3. **He\u2019s Being Friendly**: Sometimes, people look at others to be approachable or friendly, especially in social settings.  \n\n4. **It\u2019s Coincidental**: He might not even realize he\u2019s doing it\u2014it could be a habit or just a reflex.  \n\n5. **He\u2019s Shy**: If he\u2019s interested but nervous, he might look at you and then quickly look away.  \n\nTo get a clearer idea, pay attention to other cues:  \n- Does he smile or make eye contact when he looks?  \n- Does he try to initiate conversation or find ways to be near you?  \n- Are there other signs of interest, like compliments or body language (e.g., leaning in, mirroring your actions)?  \n\nIf you\u2019re interested in him, you might consider giving him a subtle signal (like a smile or hello) to see how he responds. If you\u2019re unsure, time and more interactions will usually reveal his intentions!",
